						<p>Yes, little boys get their confidence set or solidified, or not, at around age 7. And this leads either to maturity or neurosis - the sad state wives often call 'a boy in a man's body'. cassant describes it very well.<br />
Therapy, tragedies and yes beatings can all shatter one's confidence, providing the opportunity to rebuild it, and when rebuilding one will often reach a plateau and stay there.<br />
But please don't say one can NEVER get to maturity after a neurotic start. It is very rare but it can be done, and it takes a very long time.</p>
